{
  "texts": [
    "Information about conflicts of interest and funding was not explicitly stated in 23 (n = 23/89, 25.8%) studies, while 48 (n = 48/89, 53.9%) reported that there were no conflicts of interest or funding.",
    "A total of 18 (n = 18/89, 20.2%) studies reported the presence of conflicts of interest and funding 13, 24, 38, 40, 54, 58, 59, 67, [69] [70] [71] 74, 80, 84, 96, 103, 105, 111.",
    "Most studies did not report information about the institutional review board (IRB) approval (n = 55/89, 61.8%) or deemed IRB approval unnecessary (n = 28/89, 31.5%).",
    "Six studies obtained IRB approval (n = 6/89, 6.7%) 52, 82, [84] [85] [86] 92.",
    "An overview of the presence of codes for each study is provided in the Supplementary Dataset file 3."
  ]
}